projectInfo.name: Sawla (N7)  to Tuna (N12), Ghana #Leclara #liei-larabanga
projectInfo.shortDescription:
Please contribute to this (and other) project(s) for the "Lets Map with her" international mapathon and to support other longer term goals of area development.


>==> When working with __JOSM__ (recommended!) please remember to use __ONLY__ the __project _default_ imagery__. (_These may be greyscale (black and white) or coloured_). 

>==> For __ID-Editor__, please  choose __Custom__ imagery (when available). _Otherwise_ use __Maxar Premium__ but only if it __not__ identical to the Bing imagery! 
==> __DO NOT use Bing__ or any other sources as they are _completely outdated_.

To map: __Buildings__, __Roads__ and __Water__ (ponds or reservoirs and clearly identifiable waterways, etc. often 'intermittent=yes'.)  As necessary, use `building=construction`. (These appear as grid-like patterns on the ground.)

==> __Read the important further _Project Instructions_ BEFORE you begin to map__ (or validate). Use of JOSM for mapping is strongly recommended. Thanks!
projectInfo.description:
You are kindly asked to familiarize yourself with the following instructions before you begin.
>==> When working with __JOSM__ (recommended!) please remember to use __ONLY__ the __project _default_ imagery__. (_These may be greyscale (black and white) or coloured_).  

>==> For __ID-Editor__, please  choose __Custom__ imagery (when available). _Otherwise_ use __Maxar Premium__ but only if it __not__ identical to the Bing imagery!
==> __DO NOT use Bing__ or any other sources as they are _completely outdated_.


There are some round huts, mostly in rural areas. Otherwise, do not forget to square building corners (not a problem if you use JOSM's "Buildings Tool" to map.) You will only occasionally find buildings which do not have right-angle corners.
Note that there may be numerous buildings in towns (or otherwise) requiring a relation of `type=multipolygon` (with roles "outer","inner").

As necessary, use `building=construction`. (These appear as grid-like patterns on the ground.)

The major paved (national) highways in the area (N7,N12 and/or N10) are already mapped.
Otherwise, map clearly visible roads, tracks and paths connecting towns and settlements. Other highways clearly connecting between towns and settlements can be marked `highway=unclassified` but many should be labelled as either `highway=track` if it looks like traffic can pass, otherwise `highway=path`. 

Don't _overwork_ yourself! Do __NOT__ map the very many tracks or paths which end in farming fields (or "the middle of nowhere").

In populated areas: `highway=residential`. Important footpaths in towns may be tagged `highway=path`. Again, _don't exaggerate_. It is _not_ necessary_ to trace every way or path _within_  smaller towns or villages: a few "major" ones are really sufficient.

When possible, try to use Replace Geometry (instead of Deleting) if you have to correct specific objects previously mapped with much older satellite images.

The use of JOSM for mapping is _highly_ recommended.
